5|$|The International Covenant on Economic, Social and <b>Cultural</b> <b>Rights</b> (ICESCR) is a {{multilateral}} treaty {{adopted by the}} United Nations General Assembly on 16 December 1966, and in force from 3 January 1976. It commits its parties to work toward the granting of economic, social, and <b>cultural</b> <b>rights</b> (ESCR) to the Non-Self-Governing and Trust Territories and individuals, including labour rights {{and the right to}} health, the right to education, and the right to an adequate standard of living. As of 2015, the Covenant has 164 parties. A further six countries, including the United States, have signed but not ratified the Covenant.|$|E
